.\" termin.al-name: help
.\" termin.al-usage: help
.\" termin.al-summary: Show commands grouped by purpose.
.TH HELP 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
help \- Show commands grouped by purpose.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
help
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Builds a terminal command index from the live registry and writes it to the current pane's scrollback. Commands are grouped as GNU-like, application and navigation commands; each row uses the registered summary and includes aliases when present.
.SH OUTPUT
The output is plain terminal text with NAME, SYNOPSIS, COMMANDS, EXAMPLES and SEE ALSO headings. It is a compact index, not the full generated manual corpus.
.SH FAILURES
Any argument is rejected.
.SH NOTES
Use man(1) to open the complete reference for one registered command. Unquoted and unescaped redirections support descriptors 0 through 9 with
.BR < ,
.BR > ,
.BR >> ,
.BR <> ,
.BR <& ,
.BR >&
and
.BR >| .
Redirections belong to each command before pipelines and command lists. Redirected files are shared by all panes and persist in browser-local storage; no host filesystem is accessed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ help
$ man open
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
man(1)
